text:
On this #WorldWetlandsDay, I am extremely delighted to share the designation of two more Ramsar sites, Sakkarakottai and Therthangal Bird Sanctuaries in Ramanathapuram District, increasing the number of #Ramsar sites in Tamil Nadu to 20, the highest in the country, with 19 sites designated subsequent to the launch of the Tamil Nadu #WetlandsMission in 2021.

Our #DravidianModel Government remains committed to conserving wetlands and will continue to take proactive steps to protect our rich natural heritage.

